author: @Seeker265729
text: I'm pretty sure that on_step refers to the each discrete moment of game time which is some fraction of a second (note the game time in the in game timer).  I believe that sc2 can normally accept a certain number of simultaneous command inputs (or actions) per unit of game time (possibly per player?) Professional gamers can peak at maybe 500 actions per minute.  Pretty sure as others have mentioned that python is asynchronously sending the command to build probes as fast as it can, which is happening faster than the game can check the on_step hence queueing up 2 when the condition is true
